name: Feedback
relation: can be a form of output for a system that receives input

name: Data
relation: is often an outcome or result of processing input through various operations and can lead to further outputs

name: Signal
relation: can be produced as a consequence of output from a system's internal processes, representing a form of communication between components of the system

name: Product
relation: is often an outcome or result that is generated after input and processing, hence its relation to Output
